theorem
Th50: (I is (implicative-ideal of X) iff (for x,y being (Element of X) holds (( x \ ( y \ x ) ) in I implies x in I)))
proof
A1: ((for x,y being (Element of X) holds (( x \ ( y \ x ) ) in I implies x in I)) implies I is (implicative-ideal of X))
proof
assume A2: (for x,y being (Element of X) holds (( x \ ( y \ x ) ) in I implies x in I));
A3: (for x,y,z being (Element of X) holds ((( ( x \ ( y \ x ) ) \ z ) in I & z in I) implies x in I))
proof
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X),z being (Element of X);
assume (( ( x \ ( y \ x ) ) \ z ) in I & z in I);
then ( x \ ( y \ x ) ) in I by BCIALG_1:def 18;
hence thesis by A2;
end;
( 0. X ) in I by BCIALG_1:def 18;
hence thesis by A3,CKB59:def 1;
end;
(I is (implicative-ideal of X) implies (for x,y being (Element of X) holds (( x \ ( y \ x ) ) in I implies x in I)))
proof
assume A4: I is (implicative-ideal of X);
let x being (Element of X),y being (Element of X);
assume ( x \ ( y \ x ) ) in I;
then A5: ( ( x \ ( y \ x ) ) \ ( 0. X ) ) in I by BCIALG_1:2;
( 0. X ) in I by A4,CKB59:def 1;
hence thesis by A4,A5,CKB59:def 1;
end;
hence thesis by A1;
end;
